ğŸ³ 1. "Site canâ€™t be reached" or Frontend doesnâ€™t load

Cause:
The frontend container may not be running, or the port is not correctly mapped.

Fix:

docker ps


Check if the container is listed. You should see:

frontend-container   ...   0.0.0.0:8080->80/tcp


If not, start it manually:

docker start frontend-container


If that fails, rebuild it:

docker rm -f frontend-container
docker build -t frontend:latest ./frontend
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name frontend-container --network app-network frontend:latest


Then, visit:
ğŸ‘‰ http://localhost:8080

ğŸ”Œ 2. â€œFailed to load backend message.â€ when clicking â€œFetchâ€

Cause:
The frontend cannot reach the backend container.

Fix:

Ensure the backend container is running:

docker ps


You should see:

backend-container   ...   3000/tcp


Verify both containers share the same Docker network:

docker network inspect app-network


You should see both containers under "Containers".

If one is missing, reconnect it:

docker network connect app-network backend-container
docker network connect app-network frontend-container


If still failing, rebuild both containers:

docker rm -f backend-container frontend-container
docker build -t backend:latest ./backend
docker build -t frontend:latest ./frontend
docker run -d --name backend-container --network app-network -p 3000:3000 backend:latest
docker run -d --name frontend-container --network app-network -p 8080:80 frontend:latest

âš™ï¸ 3. â€œError: Conflict. The container name ... is already in useâ€

Cause:
You tried to start a new container with a name that already exists.

Fix:
Remove the old container first:

docker rm -f frontend-container backend-container


Then rerun your build and run commands.

ğŸŒ 4. Frontend Fetch Works Locally but Not in Browser

Cause:
The frontend HTML is using an internal Docker hostname (backend-container) that browsers outside the container canâ€™t resolve.

Fix Options:

Option A (Recommended):
Use Docker Compose to manage both services:

docker-compose up --build


This ensures the services share a network and use service names automatically.

Option B:
Change the fetch URL in index.html temporarily for local testing:

const res = await fetch('http://localhost:3000/');

